text.tspan: Pure-Play Wealth Management
Charles Schwab
- COO commentary during January '23 investor meeting that SCHW is working to prepare to take advantage of advanced analytic
capabilities that preceed AI.
- Capabilities include Next Best Conversation which assists service professionals and Schwab Intelligent Assistant, an online chat
bot.
- View AI and machine learning as tools that can scale human professionals and deliver a better personalized experience via digital
- SCHW Advisor Services leverages an AI-enhanced voice technology to route incoming RIA calls
- SCHW noted 40 AI use cases in various stages of development, including some already in use
- Two-pronged AI strategy: 1) Near-term focus, powering client-facign representatives and making interenal teams more efficient; 2)
long-term vision, meaningfully enhanced client service and enabling more personalized client interactions
LPLA Financial
- LPLA invests heavily in tech investment to drive efficiencies and growth for advisors through tools such as the Adversiting Review
Tool, which reduces content approval time and speeds up the marketing process through embedded AI.
- in 2024 LPLA plans to roll out its ClientWorkd Rebalancer, a dynamic trading and rebalancing system that can be used by practices
of all sizes, affiliations and sophistications.
- LPLA launched Practice Hub, a performance optimization solution, in 2q23. The capability delivers comprehensive data in a
structured format, so advisors can better understand their performance on a relative and absolute basis.
- AI has already been applied to a number of compliance review workflows which has improved review efficiency and overal risk
management efficacy
LPLA indicated a preference to let larger firms with bigger tech budgets figure out the best ways to use this technology, which LPL
could ultimately leverage. Despite this more tempered approach, LPLA has employed some use cases, including the "AI Advisory
Solutions" program designed to improve advisor efficiency
In Apr '25, LPLA appointed Vaughn Harvey as executive vice president and chief data and artificial intelligence (AI) officer
Raymond James
- Per the CEO, RJF has been using AI for a number of years but doesn't anticipate meaningful revenue gains as a result of using AI.
- Have a live tool that helps advisors identify opportunities in portfolios. RJF does not see AI as a means to replace the advisor, but
rather as a tool that can be leveraged.
- Mgmt commented that it plans to continue to endeavor tech strategy around data and incorporate ML, AI, and data science in order
to position for the next 8-to-10 years. Central to this strategy is supporting the advisor's ability to serve clients.
- AI has already been implemented in compliance and AML. Have spent ~5 years ensuring that the data is exact and usable.
RJF has made significant financial commitments to AI technology, investing $975 million annually in technology, with AI being one
of six key investment areas of technology investment
In Apr '25 RJF launched its proprietary AI Search technology, designed for employees to answer natural-language queries from the
firm's internal knowledge base. The firm also utilizes AI cypersecurity tools to defend systems and protext data
Robinhood
- HOOD has made commentary that AI will create a strategic shift in how the business will be operated and CEO Vladimir Tenev has
made commentary stating that "every company will need to become an AI company."
- The firm's modern tech stack as well as their track record of innovation positions HOOD for the potential to be an early leader in
financial services for AI. The firm is actively engaged in recruiting high-quality talent to lead AI efforts.'
HOOD launched Robinhood Cortex, an AI-powered trading assistant providing traders up-to-date news and market data
Mgmt sees AI as fundamentally transforming the financial industry. CEO has discussed how AI could enable "sophisticated
autonomous financial agents" that can perform tasks on behalf of users
